Preheat your barbeque, make sure it is on low when cooking the pork.
Start basting right away with the reserved marinade to start developing the flavors.
The pork should be done in 15 - 20 minutes. With an internal temperature of 145 ºF

Name: Filipino BBQ Pork Skewers

Cut the pork into 3 inch cubes.
Salt the pork all over.
Set your pressure cooker to sauté mode and add avocado oil.
Once the oil is hot, carefully sear the pork on all sides until a golden-brown crust forms.
Remove the pork from the pressure cooker and set it aside.
In the same pressure cooker add the smashed garlic, peppercorn paste. Sauté until they become fragrant.
Add the quartered onion and saute for another 1 minute.
In a bowl, combine pineapple juice, soy sauce, sweet soy sauce, vegan oyster sauce, brown sugar, and sesame oil. Mix well until the sugar is dissolved.
Pour the prepared sauce over the pork, ensuring it's well-coated.
Return the seared pork to the pressure cooker, placing it on top of the aromatics.
Seal the pressure cooker and set it to high pressure for about 60 minutes, depending on your device.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Crispy Asian Pulled Pork
Description: Get ready for this amazing Crispy Asian Pulled Pork Recipe! Think juicy pulled pork, super crispy, and loaded with tasty Asian vibes. Made in the Instant Pot or an pressure cooker, this easy to make but unforgettable dish will have you licking your bowl.

ingredients.Name: each salt and pepper or dry spiced rub
BBQ sauce (You can use your own homemade bbq sauce or use your favorite BBQ sauce from the grocery store)

Program to MEAT for 50 minutes.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Instant Pot Ribs with Apple Juice
Description: Melt in your mouth tender. These Instant Pot Pork Ribs with Apple Juice will blow your mind. Super to make, have delicious fall-off-the-bone ribs in less than 1 hour.

directions.Direction: Prepare the glaze: In a small saucepan, combine the maple syrup, brown sugar, bourbon, lemon slices, ginger, and salt. Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until the mixture comes to a gentle boil. Let it cook for about 8 minutes until it begins to thicken slightly. Remove from heat—it will continue to thicken as it cools.
Roast the ham: Preheat your oven to 325°F (165°C). Place the spiral ham in a roasting pan, cut side down, and brush generously with the glaze.

Baste as it cooks: Roast the ham for about 12 minutes per pound (approximately 1 hour for a 5 lb ham). Every 15 minutes, brush the ham with more glaze to build up layers of flavor and create a caramelized coating.
Broil for a perfect finish: During the last 5 minutes of cooking, switch your oven to broil. Keep a close eye to ensure the glaze bubbles and caramelizes without burning.
Serve and enjoy: Remove the ham from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing. Serve with extra glaze on the side for drizzling or dipping.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Maple Bourbon Ham
Description: Get ready to steal the show with this Maple Bourbon Ham! It’s sweet, savory, a little boozy, and absolutely perfect for any holiday table. The sticky maple glaze is loaded with bourbon, tons of ginger, and lemon to bring it all together. Trust me, this ham is the MVP of family dinners, holiday feasts, or any time you just want to impress without breaking a sweat.

ingredients.Name: pieces of large prawns (peeled, deveined, and butterflied)
cilantro stalks (cleaned and leaves and stalks removed)
Sauce for dipping: sweet Thai chili sauce

directions.Direction: Marinate the Prawns: Place the peeled, deveined, and butterflied prawns in a large mixing bowl.

Prepare the garlic cilantro paste: In a pestle and mortar or a food processor, combine the garlic, cilantro stalks, black peppercorns, and salt. Smash until it forms a paste if using a pestle and mortar. Pulse the mixture until it forms a coarse paste if using a food processor.
Coat the Prawns: Mix the paste in with the shrimp. Sprinkle cornstarch and coat the prawns evenly.

Fry the Prawns: Carefully lower the marinated prawns into the hot oil using a slotted spoon or tongs. Fry in batches to avoid overcrowding. Fry the prawns for about 3-4 minutes, or until they turn golden brown and crispy. Use a slotted spoon to remove the prawns and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to absorb any excess oil.
Serve and Enjoy: Garnish your Crispy Thai Butterflied Prawns with the cilantro leaves and thai red chili peppers for a fresh and vibrant touch. Serve hot with your favorite dipping sauce.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Crispy Thai Butterflied Shrimp
Description: This Crispy Thai Butterflied Shrimp is loaded with flavors. With only six ingredients, this crispy goodness is perfect if you need something quick in less than 15 minutes. Definitely, better than takeout.

ingredients.Name: stalk of green onions (white and green separated)

directions.Direction: Prep your salmon. Pat dry with a paper towel.
Prep ingredients. Mince the garlic, julienne the ginger, and slice the green onions.
In a bowl, combine all the ingredients and combine.
Marinate the salmon for 10 to 30 minutes.
Preheat your air fryer or oven to 375 degrees. Line your air fryer tray or basket with parchment paper.
Place your salmon fillets and put the sauce on top.
Air fry at 375 degrees for 8 minutes. Broil for 2 minutes for that gorgeous crust on the top.
Let the salmon rest for 5 minutes. Serve and enjoy!

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Asian Salmon Recipe
Description: This Asian Salmon recipe is so good! I am not just saying that. The perfectly balanced flavors make this dish glorious at every bite. It is so easy to make, just combine and air fry. Don't have an air fryer? Use your oven! It will take longer than 12 minutes but it will still come out delicious.

ingredients.Name: pieces of peeled and deveined shrimp
of frozen vegetables (corn, peas and carrots)
stalks of green onions (white and green parts separated)
of neutral oil (I used avocado oil)

directions.Direction: Ensure prawns are peeled and deveined.
Season prawns with a pinch of salt and pepper.
Use day-old rice for better texture.
Break up any clumps to ensure even cooking.
Dice green onions, separating the white and green parts.
Heat a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add 2 tablespoons of neutral oil to the pan.
Toss in minced garlic cloves.
Add prawns and cook until they turn pink and opaque.
Remove prawns and set aside.
Add more oil to the pan. Saute the minced garlic until lighty golden brown.
Add the day-old rice to the wok, breaking up any clumps.
Make a well in the middle. Add eggs into the well.
Scramble the eggs until just set.
Mix the eggs with the rice.
Stir in white parts of the green onions.
Add frozen vegetables and stir-fry until they are heated through.
Pour soy sauce and sesame oil over the rice, stirring to combine.
Add the cooked prawns and eggs back into the wok, mixing well.
Toss in the green parts of the onions and 1 tablespoon of butter.
Stir-fry everything together until well combined and heated through.
Spoon the delicious shrimp fried rice onto serving plates.
Garnish with extra green onions.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Easy Shrimp Fried Rice Recipe - better than takeout
Description:
Enjoy our tasty and best Shrimp Fried Rice! It's a mix of juicy shrimp, colorful veggies, and perfectly cooked rice. This dish is quick, and nutritious, and you'll want to make it again and again!
 
Shrimp Fried Rice is a flexible meal, great for lunch or busy dinners. It combines shrimp, veggies, and rice for a balanced dish. Enjoy it anytime!

ingredients.Name: large prawns (about 1 pound), peeled and deveined
stalk of green onions ,white and green part separated
of chili crisp1 tbsp of fresh lemon juice2 tsp of sesame oil

directions.Direction: Peel and devein the prawns if not already done.
Finely chop the white part of the green onions and set aside. Slice the green part diagonally into thin strips for garnish.
Mince the garlic cloves.
Heat a pan over medium-high heat. Once hot, add a little oil.
Add the white parts of the green onions and garlic to the pan and sauté for about 1-2 minutes until fragrant.
Add the prawns to the pan in a single layer.
Cook for 2-3 minutes on one side until they start to turn pink, then flip them over and cook for another 2-3 minutes until fully cooked through.
Add the vegetarian oyster sauce, sweet chili sauce and chili crisp. Let it cook for 2 minutes and it should be sticky and glossy.
If you’re putting in cashews, add them now. This step is optional.
Be careful not to overcook, as prawns can become tough.
Once the prawns are cooked, garnish with the sliced green parts of the green onions.
Serve the prawns hot alongside rice and sauteed vegetables.
Enjoy your delicious prawn dish! Adjust the amount of chili crisp according to your desired level of spiciness.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Spicy Prawns Stir Fry - Easy 7 minute recipe

ingredients.Name: of cooked sushi rice (jasmine or any short grain rice will work)
pieces roasted nori seaweed (cut into 4 squares)
piece of salmon, 8 oz, skinless, cubed

directions.Direction: Preheat the oven to 400°F
Begin by cutting the skinless salmon into bite-sized cubes.
In a large bowl, place salmon cubes, soy sauce, Kewpie mayo, and sriracha. Gently mix to coat the salmon evenly with the flavors. Set aside to marinate while you prepare the other components.
In a separate bowl, combine the warmed* and cooked sushi rice, rice vinegar, and mirin. Gently fold the ingredients together.
* if using day-old rice, warm it up in the microwave for 50 seconds. It will soften up the rice.
Line the muffin tins with two pieces of roasted nori sheets diagonally, creating a small "basket" to hold the ingredients.
Spoon approximately 2 tablespoons of the prepared sushi rice into each nori-lined cup, gently pressing it down to create a base.
Top the cooked rice with the marinated salmon mixture, distributing it evenly among the cups.
Bake the salmon sushi cups at 400°F (200°C) for about 12 minutes, allowing the flavors to meld and the salmon to cook to perfection. Broil for 1-2 minutes for a crisp top.
Remove the cups from the oven and let them cool slightly.
Garnish each cup with slices of sesame seeds, avocado, chopped green onions, kewpie mayo, sriracha, and more furikake.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Viral Easy Baked Salmon Sushi Bake Cups

red miso paste (you can use white miso)

Preheat the broiler. Make sure the oven rack is 6 inches away from the broiler.

Place fish onto the tray. Use paper towels to dry the fish.
Pour half of the sauce on the fish. Broil fish for 3 minutes.

cornstarch slurry (1 tbsp cornstarch + 1 tbsp water)

directions.Direction: Rinse 2 cups of sushi rice under cold water until the water runs clear.
Cook the rice according to package instructions or in a rice cooker with 2 cups of water.

Finely chop the jalapeno (remove seeds for less heat if desired).
Combine all the chopped ingredients in a mixing bowl and toss gently to combine.
Divide the cooled sushi rice among serving bowls.
Top each bowl of rice with a portion of the marinated tuna.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: The Best Healthy Tuna Poke Bowl (30 minute recipe)

ingredients.Name: leftover cooked plain rice (sub fresh steamed rice)
sesame oil for pan frying the onigiri

directions.Direction: If you have leftover salmon, flake it into small pieces using a fork and a small bowl of water.

In a small bowl, combine the flaked salmon with 1 tablespoon of Kewpie mayo (a Japanese-style mayonnaise) and 1 tablespoon of sriracha sauce. Adjust the sriracha to your preferred level of spiciness. Mix well until the ingredients are evenly combined.
Take your leftover cooked jasmine rice and place it in a microwavable large bowl.
Heat up your rice in the microwave for 1 minute or until it is warmed and soft.
Add 2 tbsp of mirin and 2 tbsp of rice vinegar - adjust the taste to your liking.
Wet your hands with a small bowl of water to prevent the rice from sticking. Take a handful of seasoned rice and place it in your palm.
Flatten the warm rice in your hand and create a small well in the center for the salmon filling.
Add a spoonful of the creamy salmon mixture into the well.
Encase the filling with the rice and shape it into a triangle shape or oval triangular shape, whichever you prefer. Press the rice gently to ensure it holds its shape using an onigiri mold.
Place seasoned rice in the mold, filling it halfway, and create a slight hollow for your chosen fillings.
Spoon your desired filling into the hollow, then top with more rice to fill the mold completely.
Seal with the lid, and press down firmly. Uncover, invert the mold, and press the bottom button to release your onigiri.

Brush the onigiri with a little bit of sesame oil. Pan-fry the onigiri until it becomes slightly crispy and the rice develops a golden-brown crust. Place them on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
Take nori strips (nori seaweed) and wrap them around the onigiri. The nori strips will not only add a different flavor but also make it easier to hold and eat.
If desired, sprinkle some black sesame seeds, white sesame seeds, or toasted sesame seeds over the top of your onigiri for extra flavor and texture.

Creator: eatwithcarmen
Name: Easy Salmon Onigiri Recipe (Leftover salmon and rice)

stalks of green onions (separate the white from the green part)
